        "content": "<p>Miri needs a cache folder somewhere on the system. Do we have some kind of policy how official Rust projects usually pick those? Also see <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/miri/pull/774\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/miri/pull/774\">https://github.com/rust-lang/miri/pull/774</a>.</p>",
        "id": 168220739,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1560627846
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in particular we can set an \"organization\" and a \"qualifier\" which at least on macOS become a reverse domain name, so it might make sense to pick \"rust-lang\" and \"org\"?</p>",
        "id": 168220750,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1560627874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>on Linux none of this matters and on Windows only the organization is relevant</p>",
        "id": 168220755,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1560627890
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>on Linux none of this matters</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>haha. Linux users are the most vocal about this</p>",
        "id": 168222517,
        "sender_full_name": "Jake Goulding",
        "timestamp": 1560631557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no what I mean is that \"organization\" and \"qualifier\" are ignored on Linux</p>",
        "id": 168223734,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1560634022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the crate picks the right place (following XDG on Linux) automatically, you just have to fill in some blanks</p>",
        "id": 168223740,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1560634053
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>using org.rust-lang.miri would probably make sense</p>",
        "id": 168380166,
        "sender_full_name": "Luca Barbato",
        "timestamp": 1560846788
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and on unix-like $HOME/.config/miri seems sensible</p>",
        "id": 168380193,
        "sender_full_name": "Luca Barbato",
        "timestamp": 1560846822
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>.cache</code> for caches, please</p>",
        "id": 168382517,
        "sender_full_name": "Laurențiu",
        "timestamp": 1560849278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/pull/5183\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/pull/5183\">https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/pull/5183</a>. That <code>directories</code> crate should work.</p>",
        "id": 168382625,
